d music: Instead of using the main athletics stadium for the opening parade, as is customary, organisers have moved the event outside and into the heart of the capital - in keeping with their motto \\\"Games Wide Open\\\".\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 642, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the concept\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 409}, {\"ngram\": \"the main athletics stadium\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 477}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening parade\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 529}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 550}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 577}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 592}, {\"ngram\": \"their motto\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 622}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around 6,000-7,000 athletes are set to sail down a six-kilometre stretch of the river Seine from the Austerlitz bridge in the east to the Eiffel Tower, on 85 barges and boats.\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 745, \"end\": 755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 0.9947993653867981, \"rank\": 0.00522782257547673, \"text\": \"Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"6,000-7,000 athletes\", \"from\": 651, \"to\": 671}, {\"ngram\": \"a six-kilometre stretch\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 716}, {\"ngram\": \"the river Seine\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 735}, {\"ngram\": \"the east\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 774}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"85 barges\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"boats\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Up to 500,000 people are set to watch in person from specially built stands, where tickets have sold for up to 2,700 euros ($2,900), on the river banks for free, and from the overlooking balconies and apartments.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 1033, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Up to 500,000 people\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 841}, {\"ngram\": \"person\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 868}, {\"ngram\": \"specially built stands\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 896}, {\"ngram\": \"tickets\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 911}, {\"ngram\": \"up to 2,700 euros\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 943}, {\"ngram\": \"the river banks\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"the overlooking balconies\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1017}, {\"ngram\": \"apartments\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1032}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Organising a ceremony on the Seine is not easier than doing it in a stadium\\u2026 but it has more punch,\\\" chief organiser Tony Estanguet toldAFPearlier this month.\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1065, \"end\": 1070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.407621564678093e-20, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a ceremony\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1057}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1111}, {\"ngram\": \"more punch\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1134}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\" chief organiser Tony Estanguet\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1167}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because of the size and complexity of the parade, it has never been rehearsed in full.\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1282, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the size\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"complexity\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1230}, {\"ngram\": \"the parade\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1244}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The show has been designed by theatre director Thomas Jolly, a 42-year-old prodigy known for hit rock-opera musical \\\"Starmania\\\".\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1412, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The show\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"theatre director Thomas Jolly\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1343}, {\"ngram\": \"a 42-year-old prodigy\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1366}, {\"ngram\": \"rock-opera musical \\\"Starmania\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1410}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He brought on board a creative team that includes the writer of French TV series \\\"Call My Agent\\\", Fanny Herrero, as well as best-selling author Leila Slimani and renowned historian Patrick Boucheron.\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1478, \"end\": 1484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9809112535286447, \"rank\": 0.018464923721846334, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1512, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanny_Mendelssohn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.838661951537365e-14, \"text\": \"Fanny\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanny_Mendelssohn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanny_Mendelssohn\"}, {\"begin\": 1558, \"end\": 1563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leila_Arab\", \"score\": 0.9936775406775532, \"rank\": 0.004924983371839409, \"text\": \"Leila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leila_Arab\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leila_Arab\"}, {\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_Slimani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Slimani\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_Slimani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_Slimani\"}, {\"begin\": 1603, \"end\": 1612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Boucheron\", 